<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1659,1956]" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,300,1659,1685]" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">Discussion:</emphasis>
This is a very small species (body size 
<quantity box="[804,908,1660,1686]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
) as noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Spieth" box="[1078,1251,1660,1686]" firstAuthor="Spieth" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref9356" refString="Spieth, H. T. (1943) Taxonomic studies on the Ephemeroptera III. Some interesting Ephemerids from Surinam and other Neotropical localities. American Museum Novitates, 1244, 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="1943">Spieth (1943)</bibRefCitation>
, in the species description. It is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[501,603,1698,1724]" name="Suriname" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">Surinam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[615,686,1698,1724]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[745,869,1698,1724]" name="Venezuela" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Peters &amp; Dominguez" box="[880,1212,1698,1724]" firstAuthor="Peters" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" pagination="353 - 358" refId="ref9297" refString="Peters, W. L. &amp; E. Dominguez, (2001) The identity of Hagenulopsis minuta SPIETH (Leptophlebiidae: Atalophlebiinae). In: Dominguez, E. (ed.). Trends in research in Ephemeroptera and Plecoptera. Kluwer Academic / Plenum, New York, pp. 353 - 358." type="book chapter" year="2001">Peters &amp; Dominguez (2001)</bibRefCitation>
detailed variations in size, and coloration. The Venezuelan specimens are larger and the color pattern is more pronounced than the others. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spieth" authorityYear="1943" box="[284,403,1776,1801]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Hagenulopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[284,403,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="43">H. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from the other species of the genus by the following combination of characters. Imago: 1) general coloration reddish brown, heavily washed with blackish brown; 2) upper portion of male eyes separated basally, meeting medially with well developed eye bridge on inner margin of upper portion; 3) first forceps segment around 2 times length of styliger plate, and curved medially; 4) hind femora yellowish, with wide subbasal and apical dark bands; 5) cerci pale, articulations of basal 3 segments darker.
</paragraph>
